<section id="problem" class="py-24 md:py-32 bg-white">
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-6xl px-6 md:px-8">
    <h2 class="font-bold tracking-tight text-foggy-ink" style="font-size: clamp(28px, 4vw, 44px);">
      The cloud doesn't fit Africa.
    </h2>

    <div class="mt-10 max-w-3xl space-y-6 text-[17px] leading-[1.6] text-foggy-ink">
      <p>
        AWS, Azure, and Google Cloud serve Africa from Cape Town and Marseille. Two regions, an entire continent. Microsoft has 60 hyperscale campuses globally, only one in sub-Saharan Africa. New regional buildouts are unlikely — a dollar of capital in the US returns 10-20× a dollar in Lagos.
      </p>

      <p>
        So institutions in Nairobi route their AI workloads through Cape Town or Ireland. Data leaves the country. Latency runs over 100ms. Pricing is set in San Francisco. Languages most of Africa actually speaks — Kinyarwanda, Amharic, Swahili — aren't supported at production quality, even when sovereignty law (Kenya DPA 2019, Rwanda DPL) wouldn't have let them route there in the first place.
      </p>

      <p class="text-[22px] font-bold text-foggy-ink pt-4">
        Foggy fixes this by skipping the data center entirely. The compute is already in the building. We just orchestrate it.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
